Power 3 is the whole shabang. It does everything for you down to the letter. It installs ADDS, DNS and DHCP it's basically baby food.

While Power 2 changed the first script with DNS, the second script mostly does the second script with the installation and configuration in the second script. 
This is because the installation and configuration for both ADDS and DHCP is required for it too properly work.

This is for Period 1 where they can explore

autounattend.xml: Het enige wat bij de unattended XML hoeft aangepast te worden is in principe het wachtwoord. Computer naam IP's ETC, wordt allemaal automatisch gedaan in het PowerShell script.
<Password>
                    <Value>P@ssw0rd123!</Value>
                    <PlainText>true</PlainText>
                </Password>
 <UserAccounts>
                <AdministratorPassword>
                    <Value>P@ssw0rd123!</Value>
                    <PlainText>true</PlainText>
                </AdministratorPassword>
            </UserAccounts>
